<Issue id="29460" key="FAB-9560" number="9560" project="10002" reporter="kchristidis" creator="kchristidis" type="10003" summary="Provisional bootstrapper should not rely on configtxgen default" priority="3" resolution="10200" status="6" created="2018-04-17 21:01:44.0" updated="2018-07-20 14:17:30.0" resolutiondate="2018-07-20 14:05:24.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="43018"> <description><! CDATA The orderer's {{localconfig}} package uses configtxgen's {{localconfig}} package to extract the value for the default system channel name. In particular, this is used by the provisional bootstrapper, which allows an orderer to spin up w/o a genesis block.  This dependency is wrong: a core Fabric component should not have a dependency on a tool. (The dependency arrow should point the other way.)  A default value for the system channel should be defined locally, in a package contained by the orderer.  ></description> </Issue>
